Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.27,0:00:23.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A legendary instrument creates an incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.06,0:00:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The misfortunes happening to a\Nmusician family are spreading at a rapid rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.27,0:00:28.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.73,0:00:30.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the body of a child and the brains of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.40,0:00:32.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.11,0:02:00.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By Shitara Hasuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s invitation, we\Ncame to Shitara Chouichirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hasuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s request was for us to investigate the\Nmysteries surrounding the legendary Stradivarius violin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.70,0:02:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the series of mysterious\Nevents that began the year before last.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.25,0:02:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, not long after our\Narrival, the annex burst into flame.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.01,0:02:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Genzaburou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was inside, was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.84,0:02:23.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, whose cigarette was this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.93,0:02:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't look uncle uncle Kogoro's.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.39,0:02:30.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That brand looks like one of my\Ngranduncle Genzaburou's cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.19,0:02:35.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, he did\Ncome by here before heading to the annex
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.86,0:02:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.44,0:02:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.20,0:02:41.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid! Where are you're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.07,0:02:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.37,0:02:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.12,0:02:50.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was no accident; this was murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.87,0:02:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, if my reasoning is correct...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.00,0:02:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next target is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.51,0:03:03.26,Signs,,0,0,0,,The Dissonance of the Stradivarius
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.51,0:03:03.26,Signs,,0,0,0,,Interlude
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.80,0:03:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You think somebody\Ndeliberately started that fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.93,0:03:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the cause of the fire was smoking in\Nbed, and it started somewhere around this ashtray.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.06,0:03:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, if you look at these cigarettes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.90,0:03:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then at this, the cigarette that\NGenzaburou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} smoked in the main building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.86,0:03:25.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, it's the same brand and\Nthere's nothing unusual about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.33,0:03:26.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Bite marks!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.37,0:03:28.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.33,0:03:31.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Kogoro also has this habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.46,0:03:37.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he's smoking while he's working or\Nneeds to speak, he bites down on the filter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.59,0:03:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, these cigarettes don't have any bite marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.47,0:03:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you find that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.30,0:03:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.97,0:03:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to make the fire look as if it\Nwere accidentally caused by smoking in bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.81,0:03:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody smoked some cigarettes and started the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.60,0:03:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what you're trying to say, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.44,0:04:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the door to this room can\Nonly be locked from the inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.78,0:04:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would the culprit have gotten out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.24,0:04:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've figured out something\Nfor that trick too, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.53,0:04:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh, not yet
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.37,0:04:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still a little brat, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.00,0:04:17.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could just have happened to bite\Nthat one cigarette in the main building.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.50,0:04:22.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, Genzaburou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nhated having people tidy his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.80,0:04:28.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And yet, isn't it strange that we can't find any\Nother cigarettes in here that have bite marks on them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.93,0:04:35.85,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tsumagari Benio\NShitara Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.93,0:04:30.06,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That is not strange at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.39,0:04:35.85,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Whenever Genzaburou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left his room\Nhe would always bring his trash out with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.27,0:04:39.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, by the way, why did you all\Nsuddenly rush out of the room just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.19,0:04:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, actually this kid here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.40,0:04:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even if he took out his trash, I still find it strange\Nthat he'd smoke several cigarettes before going to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.86,0:04:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! People do that all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.12,0:04:54.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have dozed off while\Nhe was smoking that last cigarette!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.83,0:05:00.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if that was true, is that good enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.34,0:05:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This might turn out to be a series of murders!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.38,0:05:06.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wh-What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.30,0:05:07.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop talking rubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.84,0:05:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the names.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.26,0:05:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Danjirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was killed by the\Nburglars 30 years ago, had the initial "D".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.10,0:05:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Emi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who fell down the stairs and\Ndied two years ago, had the initial "E"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.77,0:05:23.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furuto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who fell from the\Nveranda and died one year ago, had "F".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.90,0:05:27.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, Genzaburou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who died tonight had "G"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.53,0:05:33.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"D, E, F, G". They're in alphabetical order, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.37,0:05:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, what connects all these people is that they\Nwere in this house for Shitara Chouichirou's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.92,0:05:44.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the brat said makes sense; there's something here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.67,0:05:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a moment if it goes 'D-E-F-G"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.93,0:05:52.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the next target will have the initial "H"-Hasuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.06,0:05:58.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no! It's dangerous for her to be alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.73,0:06:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? I'm the next target?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.23,0:06:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.86,0:06:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, if we follow the order of the initials...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.86,0:06:09.65,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Haga Kyousuke\NChouichirou's Nephew
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.53,0:06:10.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, if we start.\Nalphabetically from my father Danjirou,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.66,0:06:13.24,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It would be "D, E, F, G."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.87,0:06:16.37,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shitara Hasuki\NChouichirou's Granddaughter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.79,0:06:15.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on! That's just a coincidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.66,0:06:18.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.50,0:06:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless; that's a problem for tonight's requiem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.59,0:06:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Requiem?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.38,0:06:30.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a tradition in the Shitara family for somebody to play\Na requiem whenever someone in the family passes away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.93,0:06:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Up to last year, it was Genzaburou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.47,0:06:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And neither the master nor the\Nstress could do it in their present condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.77,0:06:40.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't do it either!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.60,0:06:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, why don't I perform?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.94,0:06:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you all like to join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.57,0:06:49.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not everyday that you can hear a\Nlive performance by Haga Kyousuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.99,0:06:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.11,0:06:53.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, most of the instruments were in the annex.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.20,0:06:56.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only ones left are the piano and that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.99,0:07:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, anything but that Stradivarius.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.46,0:07:01.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My hands would start shaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.92,0:07:03.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how about my violin?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.00,0:07:07.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay. I'll go down to my\Ncar and get the one I always use.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.13,0:07:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it doesn't compare with a\Nlegendary instrument made 300 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.93,0:07:16.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the one gift bequeathed to me\Nby my father. For me, it's just as good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.18,0:07:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus I don't want to have something\Nhappen to me for using that antique.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.27,0:07:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aunt Ayane would be upset if we\Nbrought it out without permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.07,0:07:28.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upset?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.40,0:07:34.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mistress has come to think\Nthat the Stradivarius is her son Furuto.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.53,0:07:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Master Furuto performed for the\Nmaster on that instrument, just before he died
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.25,0:07:44.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since that day, when the clock strikes midnight...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.51,0:07:53.47,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shitara Ayane\NChouichirou's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.93,0:08:01.73,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shitara Chouichirou\NHead of the Shitara family
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.98,0:08:05.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does Mr. Chouichirou know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.73,0:08:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The room where the Stradivarius is kept is\Nbetween my grandfather's and my grandmother's rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.32,0:08:21.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,\ I think Father's image from that time is probably\Nstill deeply imprinted in my grandmother's heart
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.73,0:08:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well now, please enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.27,0:08:49.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart's Requiem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.57,0:08:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,K. 626 in D minor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.13,0:09:13.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.80,0:09:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Uncle Kyousuke graduated from the\NGerman Music Academy at the top of his class.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.60,0:09:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, why did Kyousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} open the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.77,0:09:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably so that my grandfather\Nand grandmother could hear too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.27,0:09:29.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandmother's bedroom is directly upstairs
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.40,0:09:42.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are your grandmother's and grandfather's rooms\Nconnected by the room where the Stradivarius is kept?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.33,0:09:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my grandmother's room is locked from the\Ninside then you can!t get in from the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.00,0:09:50.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you can get in from the\Ncorridor using Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s master key.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.50,0:09:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're husband and wife yet\Nthey sleep in separate rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.34,0:09:58.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because my grandfather's a heavy\Nsmoker and my grandmother hates the smoke
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.14,0:10:01.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess he's not going to quit until he gets lung cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.93,0:10:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, if your grandfather passes\Naway, who will get the expensive violin?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.27,0:10:11.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would have been my granduncle\NGenzaburou, but now I guess it'll be my grandmother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.73,0:10:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure what my grandfather will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.45,0:10:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I'm hoping it'll be passed\Ndown to my Uncle Kyousuke, the genius musician.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, be quiet and listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.18,0:10:46.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that sound
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.20,0:11:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just now, could that have been...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.64,0:11:24.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,G-Grandmother!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.06,0:11:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quick! Call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.60,0:11:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.20,0:11:43.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The grandmother's name was Ayane. Her initial was "A".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.37,0:11:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.12,0:11:52.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody can try to take it. What's mine is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.67,0:11:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one is the storage room?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.13,0:11:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The last one on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.59,0:12:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.51,0:12:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.05,0:12:08.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's a chair beside the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.26,0:12:09.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it really suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.98,0:12:22.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, my. You're a harbinger\Nof death as always, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.11,0:12:26.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh come on, Inspector, it's just a coincidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.20,0:12:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, it's inevitable for us great detectives\Ncases always seems to occur when we're around.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:35.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which is why I wish you'd just stay put at home
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.33,0:12:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The incident occurred around\Nmidnight; she fell from that third story window.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.50,0:12:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that was her bedroom
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.47,0:12:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.30,0:12:50.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I was with everyone in the the room\Nbeneath, listening to Kyousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} perform a requiem
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.26,0:12:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Requiem?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.97,0:12:56.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it appears to be a tradition in the Shitara family.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.40,0:13:00.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, so Mr. Genzaburou who died in\Nthe fire was the youngest of three brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.90,0:13:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The oldest is Mr. Chouichirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.74,0:13:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the son of the second brother who died 30 years\Nago, Mr. Danjirou, is this Kyousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} you mentioned
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.66,0:13:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what do you think was the\Nmotive for suicide then, oh great detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.12,0:13:14.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, ah, I'm still working on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.33,0:13:17.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The motive was probably the violin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.67,0:13:20.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, she is the Shitara family butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.67,0:13:25.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, come with me to the mistress room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.30,0:13:29.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-This is the Stradivarius!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.26,0:13:34.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be burglars broke in again\Nd during the struggle with Ayane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.64,0:13:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this room was locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.52,0:13:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there doesn't appear to be any sign of a struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.31,0:13:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And no signs of any people entering or leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.90,0:13:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody must have broken it before the\Nmistress even opened the case. What a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.78,0:13:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bu-But, it's just a broken instrument...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.66,0:13:56.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you realize? This is a legendary\Nviolin worth hundreds of millions of yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.00,0:14:02.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in Ayane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s heart it was almost\Nlike a replacement for her late son Furuto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.92,0:14:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She must have decided to jump\Nwhen she found it had been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.80,0:14:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.18,0:14:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that lady broke it herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.14,0:14:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This brat again...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.72,0:14:16.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She' broke it herself? Why do you think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.52,0:14:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, see the new scratches on this table?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.77,0:14:22.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must have been from\Nwhen the old lady smashed the violin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.65,0:14:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot, she wasn't clueless like the inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.78,0:14:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why on earth would Ayane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nbreak such a valuable instrument?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.45,0:14:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's what I would think too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.54,0:14:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this was real, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.58,0:14:38.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.50,0:14:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, look at the label inside the violin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.92,0:14:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mark says GA
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.84,0:14:54.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was really made by Antonio\NStradivari, wouldn't it be marked with A.S.?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.73,0:15:01.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? How do you know so much about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.52,0:15:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, it's because\NShinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} taught me about it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.23,0:15:08.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That detective boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.44,0:15:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it Shinichi did know a lot about violins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.53,0:15:14.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably because Holmes played one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.87,0:15:18.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, what does this GA stand for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.25,0:15:20.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably the artisan who made this replica,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.87,0:15:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Used his own initials as a joke when replicating the mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.84,0:15:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,here have been hundreds of Stradivari\Nreplicas that have become famous over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.47,0:15:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, at the bottom of the\Nlabel. It says "Made in Germany."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.72,0:15:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's 100% sure this is a replica.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.60,0:15:38.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.72,0:15:41.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kyousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} I was talking about earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.85,0:15:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, who was in the room\Ndownstairs listening to him play the requiem?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.98,0:15:51.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me, Ran, the little brat there,\NHasuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the butler, Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.65,0:15:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A total of 5 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.32,0:15:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And during the performance, Ayane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.12,0:16:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would Grandmother do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.46,0:16:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Kyousuke had only just rescued her earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.67,0:16:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would she kill herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.67,0:16:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rescued her?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.13,0:16:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, during the fire, the old lady didn't escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.18,0:16:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Kyousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} that saved her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.14,0:16:21.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I still don't understand,\Nwhy would she destroy the replica?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.31,0:16:25.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that she thought it was real,\Nand just now realized that it was a replica.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.85,0:16:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.73,0:16:32.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master had the violin inspected\Nand it was certified that it was authentic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.32,0:16:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is not the real case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.20,0:16:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you looking for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.21,0:16:44.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.21,0:16:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She hid it behind the bed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.50,0:16:49.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Ayane treating it like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.67,0:16:52.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does have the mark of Antonio Stradivari.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.13,0:16:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This must be the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.30,0:16:57.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think so myself
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.64,0:16:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it okay if I play a bit to check?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.39,0:17:00.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No, I don't think that's necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.06,0:17:03.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think that it's authentic then it must be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.73,0:17:06.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, what's with that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.65,0:17:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps to surprise everyone, she bought\Nanother Stradivarius, only to find that it was a replica.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.07,0:17:18.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So she killed herself before her husband\Ncould discover that she'd wasted so much money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.03,0:17:21.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that makes sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.45,0:17:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.04,0:17:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I came into this room just now, I\Nchecked the bed and there wasn't anything there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.79,0:17:33.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody must have temporarily replaced the\NStradivarius with a replica and then secretly restored it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.26,0:17:37.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone who came into the room\Nafter I did must have, for some reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.80,0:17:38.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.05,0:17:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's so, we can find out by checking for fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.97,0:17:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now it's gotten mine all over it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.39,0:17:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plenty of mine too, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.61,0:17:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday during the day I was tuning the Stradivarius\Nin preparation for Uncle Chouichirou's birthday concert
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.19,0:17:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.86,0:18:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, afterwards I called Hasuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and handed it to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.20,0:18:05.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I practiced on it for a bit\Nhere, so my fingerprints are there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.87,0:18:07.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, was there anyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.37,0:18:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just me, my uncle Kyousuke had gone out,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.25,0:18:15.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Grandmother was in the\Ngarden so that she wouldn't disturb me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.26,0:18:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrived and while I was\Nshowing them the Stradivarius the annex caught on fire
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.72,0:18:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I took the Stradivarius that had\Nbeen left on the table to the storage room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.86,0:18:37.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This means that every one of you\Nhad a chance to switch the violin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.07,0:18:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Inspector, what does it\Nmatter considering the circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.99,0:18:43.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've got the real thing back, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.99,0:18:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the brat is just making things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.04,0:18:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's something really weird about this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.33,0:18:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on! This was a sealed room,\Nand the door to storage room was also locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.92,0:18:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's a chair right next to the open window.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.80,0:18:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how you look at it, it's definitely a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.30,0:19:01.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does this room have a spare key?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.59,0:19:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apart from the mistress' own key,\Nthere is only the master key that I carry
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.60,0:19:10.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, the key has already been found on the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.06,0:19:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.06,0:19:16.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, this isn't a series of murders at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.73,0:19:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Series of murders?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.74,0:19:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, this kid put the initials of the people who\Ndied starting 30 years ago in order to get "D, E, F, G."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.99,0:19:32.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if Genzaburou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who died in the fire is "G",\Nthen Ayane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who jumped out the window is "A".
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.00,0:19:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, there's no connection whatsoever!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.46,0:19:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Could it be a musical scale?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.51,0:19:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D, E, F, G, A. In Italian it's Do, Re, Mi...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.60,0:19:49.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in English isn't it represented as C, D, E, F, G, A, B?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.06,0:19:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't there some C-Major scale or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.27,0:20:00.07,Signs,,0,0,0,,CDEFGAB
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.52,0:19:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right That means the next letter is "B"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.19,0:20:00.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who's name starts with a "B"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.40,0:20:01.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsumagari Benio.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.32,0:20:05.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose the next B must mean me then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.03,0:20:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, I remember 30 years ago\Nwhen I started working here, the master mentioned it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.46,0:20:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said if I were one of the family, that\Nwould make a complete scale going from C to B.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.84,0:20:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right, if we start with Chouichirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nas C, we have the complete scale - C,D,E,F,G,A,B.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.47,0:20:27.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did I ever say such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.51,0:20:32.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, for the time being, could I ask\Neveryone to please wait in their rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.52,0:20:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, we've found the person's footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.19,0:20:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ft seems she jumped on her own volition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.53,0:20:42.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm, she didn't even hesitate...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.07,0:20:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, of course it's a suicide,\Nthis room was locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.03,0:20:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Locked from the inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.66,0:20:53.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, the room where Genzaburou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nburned to death was also locked from the inside
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.87,0:20:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before the fire started everyone was in the annex.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.67,0:20:59.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ali four of these people could\Nhave had the chance to start the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.67,0:21:03.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this room was also locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.51,0:21:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there must have been some way...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.30,0:21:09.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.60,0:21:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, that transparent square\Nthing at the top of the window glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.52,0:21:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, is that cellophane tape?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.90,0:21:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one on the right side too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.53,0:21:34.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Uncle Kogoro wanted me to ask if\Nanything strange fell down along with the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.00,0:21:36.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.13,0:21:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, and one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.80,0:21:46.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This piece looks like the sharp end of a chopstick.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.97,0:21:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah yes, we found some kind of burned case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.10,0:21:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's the perfect shape to hold two thin sticks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.06,0:22:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean it was empty inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.86,0:22:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, if someone used that, then it's\Npossible that Ayane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.74,0:22:10.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that remains is the mystery of the sealed rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.46,0:22:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! So this is how it was done!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.79,0:22:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's still one thing I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.46,0:22:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would they insist on doing such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.72,0:22:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.31,0:24:01.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know who the culprit is?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.27,0:24:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two years ago; the real series\Nof murders began in this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.32,0:24:11.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why do you need this\NStradivarius to solve the mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.57,0:24:13.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's just one thing I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.03,0:24:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Playing two adjoining notes causes\Na really painful sound! ...Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.33,0:24:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.91,0:24:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.83,0:24:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.12,0:24:30.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,POSTLUDE
